<div id="review_395810113" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/395810113" />
    <a title="Julio Genao" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3977017-julio-genao"><img alt="Julio Genao" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442881106p2/3977017.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/395810113?book_show_action=true">Aug 19, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julio Genao" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julio Genao" href="/user/show/3977017-julio-genao">Julio Genao</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer395810113" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2290751669878648669"><b>Remind me never to read reviews written by my most ardent &quot;fans.&quot;</b><br/><br/>This book is great, but it appears #TeamStephenson was expecting the opening of the Ark of the fucking Covenant.<br/><br/>If you want a smart, contemporary, geeky, international action thriller written by someone who just spent 10 years writing an epic about the connections between the tech of the 17th century and the tech of the 21st—in longhand, on, like, <i>parchment,</i> with a <i>fountain pen,</i> the showboating bastard—then read this.<br/><br/>It&apos;s fun. And </span>
  <span id="freeText2290751669878648669" style="display:none"><b>Remind me never to read reviews written by my most ardent "fans."</b><br /><br />This book is great, but it appears #TeamStephenson was expecting the opening of the Ark of the fucking Covenant.<br /><br />If you want a smart, contemporary, geeky, international action thriller written by someone who just spent 10 years writing an epic about the connections between the tech of the 17th century and the tech of the 21st—in longhand, on, like, <i>parchment,</i> with a <i>fountain pen,</i> the showboating bastard—then read this.<br /><br />It's fun. And funny. And damned good.<br /><br />If you want something else, put this down, walk away, and go <i>on</i> witcha bad self. Never you worry—there's bound to be a new Patterson out by Tuesday.<br /><br />That is all.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2290751669878648669" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


